.SH NAME
Window.customElements \- Window: customElements property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]customElements\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]Window\f[R] interface returns a reference to the
\f[CR]CustomElementRegistry\f[R] object, which can be used to register
new custom elements and get information about previously registered
custom elements.
.SH EXAMPLES
The most common example you\[cq]ll see of this property being used is to
get access to the \f[CR]CustomElementRegistry.define()\f[R] method to
define and register a new custom element, e.g.:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]let\f[R] customElementRegistry = window.customElements;
customElementRegistry.define(\[dq]my\-custom\-element\[dq], MyCustomElement);
.EE
.PP
However, it is usually shortened to something like the following:
.IP
.EX
customElements.define(
  \[dq]element\-details\[dq],
  \f[B]class\f[R] \f[B]extends\f[R] HTMLElement {
    constructor() {
      \f[B]super\f[R]();
      \f[B]const\f[R] template = document.getElementById(
        \[dq]element\-details\-template\[dq],
      ).content;
      \f[B]const\f[R] shadowRoot = \f[B]this\f[R].attachShadow({ mode: \[dq]open\[dq] }).appendChild(
        template.cloneNode(\f[B]true\f[R]),
      );
    }
  },
);
.EE
.PP
